            "question": "What happens to all the custom code we've written?",
            "answer": "The honest answer? Most of it becomes unnecessary. That custom integration with your commission engine? Replaced by We-Commerce Connect™. Those payment gateway wrappers? Unnecessary. The attribution tracking scripts? Built into FairShare™. You're not losing functionality—you're eliminating technical debt. The code that matters (your business logic in your commission engine) stays exactly where it is."
          }
        },
        "cto_faq_2": {
          "id": "cto_faq_2",
          "type": "faq_item",
          "name": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How do I trust a single vendor for everything?",
            "answer": "You already trust single vendors for critical systems—your commission engine, your email provider, your payment processor. The difference is that We-Commerce is designed as a platform from the ground up, not duct-taped together. Plus, your commission engine data never leaves your commission engine—Connect™ just syncs it. You maintain control of your core business data while eliminating integration complexity."
          }
        },
        "cto_faq_3": {
          "id": "cto_faq_3",
          "type": "faq_item",
          "name": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What's your API rate limiting and what happens if we exceed it?",
            "answer": "Our APIs are designed for enterprise scale with rate limits that handle hundreds of thousands of requests daily without throttling. For the 0.1% of companies that exceed standard limits, we provision dedicated infrastructure. We've never had a company outgrow our platform—we scale with you, not against you."
          }
        },
        "cto_faq_4": {
          "id": "cto_faq_4",
          "type": "faq_item",
          "name": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How do you handle data sovereignty and international compliance?",
            "answer": "We maintain regional data centers and comply with GDPR, CCPA, and local data protection regulations automatically. When you launch in Europe, data stays in Europe. Brazil data stays in Brazil. You don't manage compliance per region—it's built into the platform architecture. One less legal nightmare for your team to navigate."
          }
        },
